------------------------------------------
      | DAY 3   if,else, elif|
------------------------------------------
if statement
------------------------------------------
An example of an if statement is:

age = 18

if age < 18:
     print(' You are not 18 years old yet')
------------------------------------------
if your age is less than 18, then you are not 18 years old.

------------------------------------------
else statement
------------------------------------------
An else statement is used when the if statement is false
An example of an else statement is:

age = input()

if int(age)>= 18
     print('You are over 18 years old.')
else:
     print('You are less than 18 years old.')

------------------------------------------
elif statement
------------------------------------------
An example of an elif function is:
if name == 'Alice':
print('Hi, Alice.')
elif age < 12:
print('You are not Alice, kiddo.')
u elif age > 100:
print('You are not Alice, grannie.')
elif age > 2000:
print('Unlike you, Alice is not an undead, immortal vampire.')
------------------------------------------
an elif function is basically like an else statement, 
but there are limitations.
